--------> Available tests
1) CSDA range test for e- 
2) Stopping Power for e-
3) Radiation Yeld for e-
4) particles impinging on a target
                       (Energy deposit, transmission, backscattering,
                       (bremmstrahlung spectra, track length, 
                       (number of steps in a track, step length, proton mean range,
                       (gamma attenuation coefficient 

-------> Test Configuration

for every test: file.in 
in batch mode: file.in and file.mac

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
In file.in you can define:

1) The user must define the test type

The tests are exclusive with each other

////////////////////////////////////////////////////
   Command            |  Test Type
////////////////////////////////////////////////////
 
   #range             |  CSDA range test for e- 
   on 

   #StoppingPower     |  Stopping Power for e-
   on

   #RadiationYield    |  Radiation Yeld for e-
   on

   #Foil              |  Energy deposit, transmission, backscattering,
   on                    bremmstrahlung spectra, track length, 
                         number of steps in a track, step length, proton mean range,
                         gamma attenuation coefficient 
  
2) The user can change the following features:

///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
   Command |                        |Default configuration     | Other 
//////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

#processes |The Geant4  LowE Models |Standard model  
LowE       |are set for e-, gamma,  |for all the particles  
           |protons                 |
 
#setMaxStep|The max step for all    |the max step is not fixed |it must be set for e-
on         |the tracks is fixed     |                          |CSDA range and e-
                                                               |Stopping Power 

#Hadronic  |The hadronic            |the hadronic              |they must be set
on         |interactions are        |interactions are          |to calculate the mean 
           |switched on for protons |switched off              |proton range

______________________________________________________________________________________

How to define parameters for each test in the file.mac:

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1) e- CSDA  range, e- StoppingPower 
if the physics is Standard:             /process/eLoss/fluct false

definition of the particle:             /gun/particle e-

primary particle initial position:      /gun/position 0. 0. 0.

primary particle initial energy:        /gun/energy 0.1 MeV

primary particle direction is random:   /gun/randomDirection on 

set target material:                    /target/setTargetMat Hydrogen

the target must be a box:               /target/setTargetThick 1500. cm
                                        /target/setTargetX 1500. cm
                                        /target/setTargetY 1500. cm
                                        /target/update

the Max Step must be fixed:            /target/setMaxStep 0.001 cm
(1/100 of the theorical range value) 

Cut in range high:                     /le/cutE 1. m
No interest in secondary particles

for the tracking:                     /tracking/storeTrajectory 1
beamOn :                              /run/beamOn 1 
the e- CSDA or Stopping Power value 
is fixed. One event is ok

/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2) Energy deposit, transmission, backscattering,
   bremmstrahlung spectra, track length, 
   number of steps in a track, step length, proton mean range,
   gamma attenuation coefficient 

The test configuration consists in a beam impinging a target;
il the file.mac you can define:

1)for the tracking:             /tracking/storeTrajectory 1
2)the target thickness:         /target/setTargetThick 5. mm
                                /target/update
3)the target material:          /target/setTargetMat  Silicon
                              
4) the cut in range:            /le/cutE 0.1 micrometer
if you are interested in
secondary particles info
(cut lower, more info on
 secondary particles)

5)the primary particle:        /gun/particle gamma
 (e-, e+, gamma, proton)

6)the primary particle energy: /gun/energy 10. MeV

7)the number of events:        /run/beamOn 1000000
1000000 for each configuration

________________________________________________________________________

--------->Output

1) CSDA range test for e- : Range.txt 
2) Stopping Power for e-  : StoppingPower.txt
3) Radiation Yield for e-  : radiationYield.txt
4) particles impinging on a target : test50.hbk
                                     Transmission.txt

                       